div.p:
It is true you tell me, that the Commission, Matth. 28. is not peculiar to the
Apostles, and that therefore it does not Evidence, they were Extraordinary Officers;
for (say you) There is indeed a Charge given them to Baptize and Teach,
but it seems a wonderful way of proving them to be Extraordinary Officers, from
the Authority they had to do that which any Ordinary Minister may do: and
that by vertue of this Commission.
